               <p>ROBERT FULLER. I left my plane at an unfinished house on the 20th of August - I missed it on the 22d - the prisoner worked for my master; I asked if he had seen it- he said No; I found it at Gideon's, the pawnbroker's, on that day; I told the prisoner I had found it, and asked him to go with me - he said he would - he ran away and I pursued him - an officer was sent for.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q. Did not I offer you a book till I got the plane out, and tell you what induced me to take that liberty with it? A. He offered me a book after he tried to give me the slip.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260914-223-person1267">
